    {
      "text": "[CHARACTER CREATION - Opening]\n\n**Firebase Sanity Check:** System initialized with prompt-derived context. Character: Practical Ranger. Setting: Ruined Observatory. System: D&D 5E SRD.\n\n**CAMPAIGN SUMMARY**\nTitle: The Watch at the Ruined Observatory\nCharacter: Practical Ranger (Pending Creation)\nSetting: A crumbling frontier observatory battered by a relentless storm.\nDescription: A vigil at the edge of civilization, where the sky meets the smoke of distant campfires.\nAI Personalities: Pragmatic, Vigilant, Atmospheric\nOptions: AIGenerated, StandardDND, CustomClass\n\nWelcome to the frontier. Before we begin the watch on this stormy night, we must define the ranger who holds the line. Please select your preferred character creation method below.",
      "actor": "gemini",
      "sequence_id": 2
    },
    {
      "text": "Start Adventure",
      "mode": "character",
      "actor": "user",
      "sequence_id": 3
    },
    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "Night (20:00:00) at the Ruined Observatory\u2014the sky is a bruised purple, torn apart by jagged streaks of lightning that illuminate the crumbling frontier for heartbeats at a time. Rain lashes horizontally through the shattered dome of the observatory, turning the centuries-old dust on the floor into a slick, grey slurry. \n\nAric (Lvl 1) huddles beneath the skeletal remains of a great brass telescope, his cloak heavy and sodden. The wind howls like a wounded beast through the stone arches, drowning out all but the loudest cracks of thunder. Beyond the precarious ledge of the observatory, the frontier stretches out into the gloom. Far below, masked by the downpour, thin trails of smoke rise from distant campfires\u2014or perhaps the remains of a village. \n\nYou strain your eyes against the driving rain, but the elements are a thick curtain. The darkness feels heavy, pressing in on the ruined walls, and though you see no movement yet, your instincts as a ranger prickle. Something out there, amidst the smoke and the storm, feels out of place.",
      "sequence_id": 4,
      "actor": "gemini"
    },
    {
      "text": "Start Adventure",
      "mode": "character",
      "actor": "user",
      "sequence_id": 5
    },
    {
      "mode": "character",
      "text": "You rise from your crouched position beneath the telescope's skeleton, shaking water from your cloak. That prickle at the back of your neck won't leave you. Years on the frontier have taught you to trust such feelings.\n\nMoving carefully along the observatory's broken floor, you pick your way to a gap in the stonework where a window once looked out over the eastern slope. The rain is relentless, hammering against the ancient stones, but you press your face close to the opening and peer into the gloom.\n\nAt first, there's nothing but the storm\u2014trees bendingHorizontal in the wind, the distant shapes of hills swallowed by darkness. Then lightning splits the sky, and for one heartbeat, the world turns bright as noon.\n\nYou see it. Halfway down the slope, barely visible against the dark earth\u2014movement. Something that shouldn't be there. A shape that doesn't belong to the landscape. It's there and gone in a flash, but the image burns into your memory.\n\nSomething is approaching the observatory.",
      "sequence_id": 6,
      "actor": "gemini"
    }
  ],
